---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service | Gutterbugs Exterior Cleaning"
  description="Full Terms of Service for Gutterbugs LTD — exterior cleaning, gutter clearing, roof cleaning, and pressure washing across Hertfordshire and Buckinghamshire."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-white pt-32 pb-12 relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-sky-900/20 to-transparent pointer-events-none"></div>
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 relative z-10">
      <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-sky-500/10 border border-sky-500/30 rounded-full px-4 py-1.5 mb-4">
        <span class="text-sky-600 text-sm font-medium">Legal</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;">
        Terms of Service
      </h1>
      <p class="text-gray-600">
        Last updated: 23 April 2026 · Gutterbugs LTD (Company No. <strong class="text-gray-900">14118756</strong>)
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Terms Content -->
  <section class="pb-20 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 space-y-10">

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern all services provided by <strong class="text-gray-900">Gutterbugs LTD</strong>
        (trading as <strong class="text-gray-900">Gutterbugs Exterior Cleaning</strong>) to the customer ("the Client"). By accepting
        a quotation — in writing, by email, or by allowing work to proceed — the Client confirms they have read,
        understood, and agree to be bound by these Terms.
      </p>

      <!-- 1. Definitions -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 pb-2 border-b border-gray-200" style="font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;">1. Definitions</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed list-disc list-inside">
          <li><strong class="text-gray-900">"Gutterbugs", "we", "us", "our"</strong> — Gutterbugs LTD, registered in England and Wales.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-gray-900">"Client", "you", "your"</strong> — the person, company, or other party engaging our services.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-gray-900">"Services"</strong> — exterior cleaning works including (but not limited to) gutter clearing, roof cleaning, pressure washing, soffit/fascia cleaning, conservatory cleaning, and solar panel cleaning.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-gray-900">"Property"</strong> — the address at which the Services are to be carried out.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-gray-900">"Quotation"</strong> — the written quote issued to the Client setting out the scope and price of the Services.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- 2. Quotation & Agreement -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 pb-2 border-b border-gray-200" style="font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;">2. The Quotation & Agreement</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Each Quotation is valid for 30 days from the date of issue. Acceptance of the Quotation forms a binding
          contract between the Client and Gutterbugs LTD on these Terms. The Quotation, together with these Terms,
          forms the entire agreement and supersedes any prior discussions, representations, or correspondence.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          Variations to the agreed scope of work will be discussed and confirmed in writing (including email or messaging app)
          before any additional work is undertaken. Additional charges may apply.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- 3. Access & Site -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 pb-2 border-b border-gray-200" style="font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;">3. Access & Site Requirements</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">The Client agrees to:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed list-disc list-inside mb-4">
          <li>Provide safe and unobstructed access to the Property on the scheduled service date.</li>
          <li>Provide access to a suitable water supply (an outdoor tap) and a 240V power outlet as required for our equipment.</li>
          <li>Ensure all windows, doors, vents, skylights, and roof fixtures are properly closed and sealed before work commences.</li>
          <li>Move vehicles, garden furniture, decorative items, and other fragile or valuable possessions clear of the work area.</li>
          <li>Notify us in advance of any pets, children, or other persons who may be present during the works.</li>
          <li>Disclose any known structural defects, recent repairs, or property conditions that may affect the Services.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          Where access is denied or unsafe on the scheduled date, we reserve the right to charge for time and travel
          incurred and to reschedule the appointment.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- 4. Cleaning Methodology -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 pb-2 border-b border-gray-200" style="font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;">4. Cleaning Methodology & Client's Choice</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          We offer different cleaning methods depending on surface type, age, and condition. The specific method for
          your Property will be clearly stated on your Quotation.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">(a) Soft Wash (Manual Scrape & Biocide)</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Our recommended method for older, delicate, or fragile surfaces such as aged concrete roof tiles. This involves
          manually removing moss and then treating the surface with a professional-grade biocide. Results appear gradually
          over several months as rainfall cleanses the treated surface.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">(b) Pressure Washing</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          Provides immediate visual results but is an aggressive process. Recommended only for robust, structurally sound
          surfaces. If the Client instructs us to proceed with pressure washing on a surface that we have professionally
          assessed as aged, fragile, or otherwise unsuitable, the Client accepts that they are doing so
          <strong class="text-gray-900">at their own risk</strong> and Gutterbugs LTD is not liable for any consequent damage.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- 5. Pre-Existing Conditions -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 pb-2 border-b border-gray-200" style="font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;">5. Pre-Existing Conditions & Inherent Risks</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          The Client acknowledges that exterior cleaning services can reveal or exacerbate pre-existing, underlying issues
          with the Property. We will perform a reasonable visual inspection but cannot be held liable for the following:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed list-disc list-inside mb-4">
          <li><strong class="text-gray-900">Loose mortar, pointing, or tiles:</strong> The cleaning process, particularly pressure washing, can dislodge or remove mortar, pointing, or tiles that are already loose, cracked, degraded, or poorly fixed.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-gray-900">Sand-faced or granular tile surfaces:</strong> The Client accepts that the removal of the top "sand" or granule layer from aged concrete or sand-faced tiles is an unavoidable consequence of high-pressure cleaning. This may alter the cosmetic appearance and porosity of the tiles.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-gray-900">Water ingress:</strong> While we take all reasonable care, we are not liable for water ingress or resulting damage from poorly sealed windows, doors, vents, roof fixtures, or other structural defects.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-gray-900">Aged or rusted gutter brackets and downpipes:</strong> Cleaning may dislodge fixtures that are already failing due to age, corrosion, or poor installation.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-gray-900">Vegetation regrowth:</strong> Moss, algae, and lichen will eventually return as a natural process. Our biocide treatment slows but does not permanently prevent regrowth.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          Gutterbugs LTD is not responsible for the cost of repairing any of the pre-existing issues listed above. We can
          recommend a trusted, independent tradesperson for any necessary repairs at the Client's expense.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- 6. Biocide -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 pb-2 border-b border-gray-200" style="font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;">6. Biocide Treatment & Results</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          As part of our cleaning process, a professional-grade biocide is applied to kill organic growth (moss, algae, lichen).
          While some results are immediate, the full self-cleansing process — aided by natural rainfall — can take several
          weeks or months to remove all residual staining. Patience is required for the best long-term results.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- 7. Photography -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 pb-2 border-b border-gray-200" style="font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;">7. Photographic & Video Documentation</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          The Client agrees to allow Gutterbugs LTD to take photographs and/or video footage of the Property before, during,
          and after the work is completed. These may be used for our internal records, for insurance purposes, and for
          marketing material (including our website, social media, and printed materials). Images will not identify the
          Property address. The Client may withdraw consent for marketing use at any time by emailing
          <a href="mailto:ryan@gutterbugs.co.uk" class="text-sky-600 hover:text-sky-700 font-medium">ryan@gutterbugs.co.uk</a>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- 8. Waste -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 pb-2 border-b border-gray-200" style="font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;">8. Waste & Debris Disposal</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">We offer two options for the disposal of waste removed during the cleaning process:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed list-disc list-inside">
          <li><strong class="text-gray-900">Option A (no additional cost):</strong> All debris bagged and placed in the Client's green waste bin, provided there is sufficient space.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-gray-900">Option B (additional fee):</strong> Removal and responsible disposal of all debris by Gutterbugs LTD for the fee specified on your Quotation.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- 9. Payment -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 pb-2 border-b border-gray-200" style="font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;">9. Payment</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Payment is due in full upon completion of the Services, by bank transfer or card. Bank details and payment
          instructions are provided on the invoice. Late payments may attract interest under the Late Payment of Commercial
          Debts (Interest) Act 1998 where applicable.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          We reserve the right to apply a deposit requirement to larger jobs (typically over £750), which will be agreed
          in writing before work commences.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- 10. Rescheduling -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 pb-2 border-b border-gray-200" style="font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;">10. Rescheduling & Adverse Weather</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          The Client may reschedule any booked appointment free of charge. We ask that you give us as much notice as
          possible so we can offer the slot to other customers.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          Gutterbugs LTD may postpone or reschedule work due to adverse weather (heavy rain, high winds, ice, snow, or
          extreme heat) for safety and quality reasons. We will notify the Client as soon as reasonably possible and
          rebook the work at the earliest mutually convenient time.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- 11. Insurance & Liability -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 pb-2 border-b border-gray-200" style="font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;">11. Insurance & Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Gutterbugs LTD holds <strong class="text-gray-900">£2 million Public Liability insurance</strong> with a reputable
          UK insurer. Where property damage or personal injury results from our negligence during the Services, claims will
          be handled through our insurance. We will provide insurance details on request.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Subject to the above, our total liability arising out of or in connection with the Services (whether in contract,
          tort, negligence, or otherwise) is limited to the amount paid by the Client for the specific Service from which
          the claim arises, except where law prohibits such limitation. This includes (but is not limited to) liability for:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed list-disc list-inside mb-4">
          <li>Death or personal injury caused by our negligence (no limit).</li>
          <li>Fraud or fraudulent misrepresentation (no limit).</li>
          <li>Any other liability that cannot lawfully be excluded or limited.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          We are not liable for any indirect, consequential, special, or economic loss (including loss of profit, loss of
          business, or loss of opportunity).
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- 12. Workforce -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 pb-2 border-b border-gray-200" style="font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;">12. Workforce & Subcontracting</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          The Services may be carried out by Gutterbugs LTD employees or by approved subcontractors operating under our
          standards, supervision, and insurance. All personnel attending the Property are appropriately trained, equipped
          with PPE, and operate in accordance with current UK Health & Safety regulations including the Work at Height
          Regulations 2005.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- 13. Cancellation -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 pb-2 border-b border-gray-200" style="font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;">13. Cancellation & Refunds</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          For Services arranged at a distance (e.g. via website or telephone), consumer Clients have a right to cancel
          within 14 days of accepting the Quotation under the Consumer Contracts (Information, Cancellation and Additional
          Charges) Regulations 2013. If the Client requests work to commence before the 14-day period ends and
          subsequently cancels, the Client may be charged for the proportion of work already completed.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- 14. Complaints -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 pb-2 border-b border-gray-200" style="font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;">14. Complaints Procedure</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          We aim to deliver a high-quality service every time. If you are unhappy with any aspect of our work, please raise
          your complaint in writing to
          <a href="mailto:ryan@gutterbugs.co.uk" class="text-sky-600 hover:text-sky-700 font-medium">ryan@gutterbugs.co.uk</a>
          within 14 days of the Service completion. We will:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed list-disc list-inside">
          <li>Acknowledge your complaint within 2 working days.</li>
          <li>Investigate and respond substantively within 7 working days.</li>
          <li>Work in good faith to resolve the matter, which may include a return visit, partial refund, or other remedy as appropriate.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- 15. Data Protection -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 pb-2 border-b border-gray-200" style="font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;">15. Data Protection</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          We process Client personal data (name, address, contact details, property details) in accordance with the UK
          GDPR and the Data Protection Act 2018, solely for the purpose of providing and administering the Services. We do
          not share Client data with third parties except where strictly necessary to deliver the Services (e.g. payment
          processors, accounting software). Clients may request access to, correction of, or deletion of their personal
          data at any time by contacting
          <a href="mailto:ryan@gutterbugs.co.uk" class="text-sky-600 hover:text-sky-700 font-medium">ryan@gutterbugs.co.uk</a>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- 16. Force Majeure -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 pb-2 border-b border-gray-200" style="font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;">16. Force Majeure</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          Neither party is liable for failure or delay in performing its obligations where caused by events beyond its
          reasonable control, including but not limited to extreme weather, natural disasters, pandemics, government
          restrictions, strikes, or supply chain failures. The affected party will notify the other promptly and the parties
          will agree a reasonable extension or alternative arrangement.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- 17. Governing Law -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 pb-2 border-b border-gray-200" style="font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;">17. Governing Law & Jurisdiction</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          These Terms and any dispute or claim arising out of or in connection with them (including non-contractual disputes)
          are governed by the laws of England and Wales. Any dispute that cannot be resolved through our complaints procedure
          will be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the English courts.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- 18. Changes -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 pb-2 border-b border-gray-200" style="font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;">18. Changes to These Terms</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          We may update these Terms from time to time. The version applicable to your contract is the version in force on
          the date of your Quotation. The latest version will always be available at
          <a href="https://gutterbugs.co.uk/terms" class="text-sky-600 hover:text-sky-700 font-medium">gutterbugs.co.uk/terms</a>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- 19. Contact -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 pb-2 border-b border-gray-200" style="font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;">19. Contact</h2>
        <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Gutterbugs LTD</p>
          <p>Trading as Gutterbugs Exterior Cleaning</p>
          <p>Registered in England and Wales · Company No. 14118756</p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            📞 <a href="tel:07904621160" class="text-sky-600 hover:text-sky-700 font-medium">07904 621160</a><br>
            ✉️ <a href="mailto:ryan@gutterbugs.co.uk" class="text-sky-600 hover:text-sky-700 font-medium">ryan@gutterbugs.co.uk</a><br>
            🌐 <a href="https://gutterbugs.co.uk" class="text-sky-600 hover:text-sky-700 font-medium">gutterbugs.co.uk</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <hr class="border-gray-200">

      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 italic">
        The summary version of these Terms appears on every Quotation issued by Gutterbugs LTD. In any conflict between
        the summary and this full version, this full version shall prevail.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
